This paper discusses energy efficient routing protocols in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on clustering routing protocols, which can also be categorized under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of MATLAB for analytical simulations suggests that the paper may also fall under Mathematical Software (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the performance metrics such as number of alive nodes, number of dead nodes, and throughput, which can be categorized under Control and Optimization (cs.SY) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
